alert.note: Alert for San Luis Obispo County Beaches; Santa Barbara County Central Coast Beaches (California) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: High Surf Advisory issued September 26 at 2:09PM PDT until September 28 at 9:00PM PDT by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...HIGH SURF ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM PDT THURSDAY... * WHAT...Large breaking waves of 10 to 14 feet, largest over northwest facing shores. Dangerous rip currents. * WHERE...Central Coast beaches of San Luis Obispo and Santa Barbara Counties. * WHEN...Until 9 PM PDT Thursday. * IMPACTS...There is an increased risk for ocean drowning. Rip currents can pull swimmers and surfers out to sea. Large breaking waves can cause injury, wash people off beaches and rocks, and capsize small boats near shore. Nuisance beach flooding and minor beach erosion may occur during the evening high tides.
info.instruction: Remain out of the water due to dangerous surf conditions, or swim near occupied lifeguard towers. Rock jetties can be deadly in such conditions, stay off the rocks.
